rComments: More difficult than I thought it would be. It turns out the class is only an easy AA+ with the bump point. Exam questions are sometimes confusing andor taken from a specific textbook passage. The vast majority of the exam is from the slides though. Expects you to read way too much. Very helpful though. Easy A-, but don't expect more than that.
Amazing professor. Extremely kind and understanding. Very power point based but encourages discussions with "bump points". Exams are easy if you read the text and slides. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!

Absolutely a wonderful person who cares about her students and wants everyone to succeed. It's unfortunate that the course material has to be taught only from the book and it's pretty boring stuff! She does what she can to make it more interesting.

Excellent prof! Managed to include relevant videos within her presentations. She always responds to emails in a timely fashion and never turns away a student asking for one-on-one time. She is fluently bilingual. Exams are tricky, as they rely heavily on specific passages from the textbook and almost always have quetions relating to the videos.

Really kind person. Cares a lot about her students and wants them to succeed. The material can be really dry at times, but she does her best to give you mental breaks by showing you neat and relevant videos. Probably one of the kindest profs I've spoken to one-on-one. Definitely get her if you can.

Nicest prof I have ever met. She basically gives you the answer if you ask her during an exam. She even gave a chance to redeem yourself if you did badly on the midterm. Her questions are often ambiguous and textbook use...she kind of just reads out of it. Her slides are just the textbook summarized

Really kind lady and a great lecturer. The only 2 things I didn't like about this class were the amount of reading required and the super long exams (3, 3 hours exams and a total of 360 questions)!!!!!

I absolutely adore her!Yes, she follows the book(like any other class) but she puts up videos to better our understanding of the material taught in class and gives ample examples not included in the book.She is very understanding & really cares about her students and I always look forward to her class.Exams follow material. I highly recommend her!

She teaches directly from the textbook, but is really knowledgable, approachable and helpful.  She has really clear expectations for exams (and they're all MCQs) and is completely reasonable with what she expects you to know.  Read the textbook and you'll get an 80 at least :)
